About Context Capital
 

Context Capital Management, LLC is an SEC-registered alternative asset management firm based in La Jolla, California and Jupiter, Florida. Our firm looks for asymmetric return profiles, opportunities where downside risk is protected and upside can be exploited. Specifically, we specialize in fixed income and relative-value strategies with a focus on event-driven credit trades. Trades are most typically constructed with long convertible and/or corporate bonds and short common stock positions. 

 



We strive to achieve consistent absolute rates of return with an emphasis on the preservation of capital via rigorous risk management and a diversified portfolio.  Context pursues a number of synergistic investment strategies with diverse themes and return drivers. Once it identifies investment opportunities, it establishes trades to isolate asymmetric return distributions. This tailored approach to investing allows Context to also construct bespoke funds or managed accounts in consultation with its clients. 

 
 





























Our Approach – Context Capital Management































 










Skip to content

























Our Approach


Universe
The global convertible bond, convertible preferred and mandatory universe has a market capitalization of nearly $500B with approximately 44% of the universe US based companies. Mr.Rosen, Mr. Fertig and Mr. Carnegie each have extensive experience managing portfolios of these securities from issuers in the US, EMEA, Japan and Asia. New issuance in the sector have been robust over the years across many different economic cycles as companies of all sizes find it advantageous to issue new bonds when volatility in the equity markets is elevated, when interest rates are high, or when fast growing smaller companies need to finance their growth.


Research
Fundamental and quantitative analysis
Leverage extensive network of business and industry contacts
Leverage internal knowledge of specific companies and industries
Maintain active dialogue with portfolio company management

Portfolio
Bottom-up selection process with adherence to diversification mandate
Cross-strategy idea generation and trade construction
Top-down capital allocation based on relative value

Controls
Rigorous risk management process Diversification and concentration limits Limited use of leverage Strict legal and compliance standards
     





























Our Team – Context Capital Management































 










