Our Team
Michael S. Rosen, CFA, Co-Chairman, Chief Executive Officer, and co-founder, is widely recognized for his expertise in managing convertible securities. Mr. Rosen was the co-principal owner of Rochester Capital Advisors, LP and FMC, Inc., the two investment advisers to The Rochester Funds, a mutual fund company specializing in the management of convertible securities and high-yield municipal bonds. From inception in 1983 to the sale of those funds to Oppenheimer Funds, Inc. in January 1996, assets under management grew to $3 billion. (Currently assets managed by the Rochester Division total more than $30 billion.) At the time of the sale, the convertible securities fund managed by Mr. Rosen had the best five-year performance as ranked by Lipper Analytical. From 1996 to 2000, Mr. Rosen served as a Portfolio Manager and President of the Rochester Division of Oppenheimer Funds, Inc. BusinessWeek named Mr. Rosen the “Best Bond Fund Manager” in 1992. Mr. Rosen has been on the Board of Trustees for the University of Rochester since 2004, where he also serves on the Investment and Development Committees. Mr. Rosen is Co-Founder, Director and Chairman of Reality Shares, Inc. Mr. Rosen was a director of Entravision (NYSE – EVC) from 2000 – 2007. During 2007 he served on the Audit Committee and the Compensation Committee. Past director positions also include Global Locate, Inc. (2000 – 2007), Danskin, Inc. (1995 – 1997) and Palmer R. Chitester Fund (2005 – 2008). He received a B.A. degree in Economics and an M.B.A. in Finance and Marketing from the University of Rochester in 1981 and 1983, respectively. Mr. Rosen is also a Chartered Financial Analyst.
William D. Fertig, Co-Chairman, Chief Investment Officer, and co-founder, has been actively involved in virtually all aspects of the U.S. convertible, high yield and equity markets. For the first nine years of his career, Mr. Fertig was a proprietary trader for E.F. Hutton and Credit Suisse. Mr. Fertig headed convertible sales at Credit Suisse and Drexel Burnham Lambert. In 1990 Mr. Fertig spearheaded McMahan Securities’ entry into the brokerage business focusing exclusively on convertible and derivative securities. As Managing Director, he oversaw the sales and trading efforts and served on the Executive and Risk Management Committees. Under Mr. Fertig’s direction, McMahan Securities grew to be one of the nation’s largest independent convertible and derivative securities dealers. Mr. Fertig has been involved in more than one hundred corporate underwritings and debt restructurings. Mr. Fertig has been a member of the Key Energy Services board of directors since 2000. He chairs the Nominating & Corporate Governance Committee, and sits on the Compensation Committee and Executive Committee. Since June of 2011, Mr. Fertig has been a trustee for ProShares and ProFunds, the world’s largest provider of leveraged and inverse funds. Mr. Fertig received a B.S. with high honors in Economics from Allegheny College, and was elected to Phi Beta Kappa. He received his M.B.A. with a concentration in Finance from New York University’s Stern School in 1985.
Charles Carnegie, CFA joined Context as a Managing Partner and Portfolio Manager in November 2015. This is Mr. Carnegie's second go-around with the Context team as he began his career here. Mr. Carnegie is coming from Hutchin Hill Capital Management, where he was a Senior Credit Analyst and Trader focused on credit and relative value opportunities including convertible, high yield and distressed corporate bonds and capital structure arbitrage. Previously, Mr. Carnegie worked at Graham Capital Management, a large macro focused hedge fund, where he worked in a similar role. Prior to Graham, Mr. Carnegie was a Distressed Analyst at Knight Capital Group while also teaching Principles of Modern Finance as an Adjunct Professor in the MBA program at Fordham University's Gabelli School of Business. Mr. Carnegie started his career at Context and was with the firm until 2008. Mr. Carnegie has BAs in Economics and Philosophy from University of Southern California and is a Chartered Financial Analyst.

  


























