Company Overview
Context Capital Management, LLC is a privately owned hedge fund sponsor. The firm also provides business consulting services to companies on matters such as corporate restructurings, capital formation, mergers and acquisitions, and management and strategic issues. It primarily provides its services to pooled investment vehicles. The firm also caters to high net worth individuals. It manages separate client-focused portfolios. The firm invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe. It invests in high yield credit, convertible preferred stocks, convertible bonds, and corporate bonds. The firm makes use of strategies such as short positions, long positions, convertible ...
Context Capital Management, LLC is a privately owned hedge fund sponsor. The firm also provides business consulting services to companies on matters such as corporate restructurings, capital formation, mergers and acquisitions, and management and strategic issues. It primarily provides its services to pooled investment vehicles. The firm also caters to high net worth individuals. It manages separate client-focused portfolios. The firm invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe. It invests in high yield credit, convertible preferred stocks, convertible bonds, and corporate bonds. The firm makes use of strategies such as short positions, long positions, convertible arbitrage, capital structure arbitrage, catalyst/event driven, relative value, credit opportunity, and fundamental overlay. It employs a combination of fundamental analysis and technical analysis with a focus on top-down and bottom-up stock picking approach to make its investments. The firm uses in-house research to make its investments. Context Capital Management, LLC was founded in 2001 and is based in La Jolla, California with an additional office in Greenwich, Connecticut.
